'''Shelob's Lair''' can refer to:
==Middle-earth==
* '''[[Shelob's Lair]]''', or ''Torech Ungol'', the lair of [[Shelob]].
==Chapters==
* ''[[Shelob's Lair (chapter)]]'', the ninth chapter of the fourth book in ''[[The Two Towers]]''.

==Adaptations==
* ''[[The Lair of Shelob]]'', the sixteenth episode of [[The Lord of the Rings (1979 radio series)|''The Lord of the Rings'' (1979 radio series)]].
* ''[[Shelob's Lair (episode)]]'', the nineteenth episode of [[The Lord of the Rings (1981 radio series)|''The Lord of the Rings'' (1981 radio series)]], aired [[12 July|July 12]], [[1981]].
* ''[[Shelob's Lair (scene)]]'', the 29th scene of ''[[The Lord of the Rings: The Return of the King]]'' and the 38th scene of [[The Lord of the Rings: The Return of the King (extended edition)|''The Lord of the Rings: The Return of the King'' (extended edition)]].
* ''[[Shelob's Lair (soundtrack)]]'', track 11 on ''[[The Lord of the Rings: The Return of the King - Original Motion Picture Soundtrack]]''.

==Other==
* [[Shelob's Lair (manuscript)]], a draft page by [[J.R.R. Tolkien]].
* "Shelob's Lair", the eighteenth set of [[Decipher Cards]], published [[March]] [[2007]].
